mcp.mobius.waila.api.IWailaEntityAccessor

    • Uses of IWailaEntityAccessor in mcp.mobius.waila.api

      Methods in mcp.mobius.waila.api with parameters of type IWailaEntityAccessor 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      List<String> IWailaEntityProvider.getWailaBody(Entity entity, List<String> currenttip, IWailaEntityAccessor accessor, IWailaConfigHandler config)
      Callback used to add lines to one of the three sections of the tooltip (Head, Body, Tail).
      Will be used if the implementing class is registered via IWailaRegistrar.registerBodyProvider client side.
      You are supposed to always return the modified input currenttip.
      List<String> IWailaEntityProvider.getWailaHead(Entity entity, List<String> currenttip, IWailaEntityAccessor accessor, IWailaConfigHandler config)
      Callback used to add lines to one of the three sections of the tooltip (Head, Body, Tail).
      Will be used if the implementing class is registered via IWailaRegistrar.registerHeadProvider client side.
      You are supposed to always return the modified input currenttip.
      Entity IWailaEntityProvider.getWailaOverride(IWailaEntityAccessor accessor, IWailaConfigHandler config)
      Callback used to override the default Waila lookup system.
      Will be used if the implementing class is registered via IWailaRegistrar.registerOverrideEntityProvider.
      List<String> IWailaEntityProvider.getWailaTail(Entity entity, List<String> currenttip, IWailaEntityAccessor accessor, IWailaConfigHandler config)
      Callback used to add lines to one of the three sections of the tooltip (Head, Body, Tail).
      Will be used if the implementing class is registered via IWailaRegistrar.registerTailProvider client side.
      You are supposed to always return the modified input currenttip.
